1
00:00:00,133 --> 00:00:01,553
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,553 --> 00:00:03,003
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:06,503
Dad.

4
00:00:06,503 --> 00:00:07,509
(Episode 12)

5
00:00:08,352 --> 00:00:09,352
Eun Ae.

6
00:00:12,580 --> 00:00:14,580
You've been through a lot, my daughter.

7
00:00:15,693 --> 00:00:16,827
I'm sorry, Dad.

8
00:00:19,493 --> 00:00:22,356
It's okay.
What matters is that you're out now.

9
00:00:24,260 --> 00:00:25,260
Eat this.

10
00:00:25,960 --> 00:00:28,293
If you eat this,
you'll never come back here.

11
00:00:32,067 --> 00:00:34,100
Cho Seong Jun, Cho Eun Ae.

12
00:00:35,904 --> 00:00:36,904
Honey...

13
00:00:40,019 --> 00:00:42,452
What are you two doing here?

14
00:00:45,660 --> 00:00:47,493
Why are you eating tofu here?

15
00:00:49,760 --> 00:00:50,793
Tell me now!

16
00:00:50,793 --> 00:00:53,020
Honey, I'll explain everything.

17
00:00:53,493 --> 00:00:56,960
This isn't something
I can explain briefly. So first...

18
00:00:56,960 --> 00:00:58,325
If it's not something
you can explain briefly,

19
00:00:58,599 --> 00:01:01,094
does that mean there's a long story
you've been hiding from me all this time?

20
00:01:01,094 --> 00:01:02,228
No, that's not it.

21
00:01:05,693 --> 00:01:06,960
Just go to work.

22
00:01:06,960 --> 00:01:07,960
You, come with me.

23
00:01:07,960 --> 00:01:09,069
- Mom.
- Come!

24
00:01:09,593 --> 00:01:11,538
Honey!

25
00:01:17,562 --> 00:01:18,612
Come on!

26
00:01:18,867 --> 00:01:20,480
What's going on?

27
00:01:21,527 --> 00:01:22,660
Eun Ae!

28
00:01:22,660 --> 00:01:24,533
- Later.
- Come inside, quickly!

29
00:01:24,533 --> 00:01:26,560
My goodness, I think she got caught.

30
00:01:26,793 --> 00:01:28,173
Caught? What do you mean?

31
00:01:29,026 --> 00:01:30,290
Do you know something?

32
00:01:33,660 --> 00:01:36,093
You foolish girl.

33
00:01:36,460 --> 00:01:39,327
You fell for a kiss
and got scammed like that?

34
00:01:39,960 --> 00:01:41,027
I'm sorry, Mom.

35
00:01:41,468 --> 00:01:43,037
Sorry?

36
00:01:43,620 --> 00:01:44,620
You...

37
00:01:45,527 --> 00:01:47,393
I regret the seaweed soup I drank...

38
00:01:47,393 --> 00:01:48,893
after giving birth to you!

39
00:01:50,325 --> 00:01:52,646
Never in my life did I imagine...

40
00:01:52,646 --> 00:01:55,765
my own child would be dragged
into a detention cell!

41
00:01:55,765 --> 00:01:58,199
And what? A seminar?

42
00:01:59,227 --> 00:02:02,693
I know how disappointed you must be
right now.

43
00:02:03,546 --> 00:02:07,005
But I couldn't just sit back
and do nothing.

44
00:02:07,493 --> 00:02:10,060
I was just trying my best
to make things right again somehow.

45
00:02:10,060 --> 00:02:12,599
Instead of trying your best,
you should've done it right!

46
00:02:13,025 --> 00:02:16,035
You asked me before
why I never trust you, right?

47
00:02:16,479 --> 00:02:19,912
This is why. Look at the mess you're in!

48
00:02:20,307 --> 00:02:21,627
Mom, what's wrong?

49
00:02:21,627 --> 00:02:22,827
- Enough.
- Why you...

50
00:02:22,827 --> 00:02:24,211
That's enough.

51
00:02:24,627 --> 00:02:29,005
Let go.
I'm going to settle this with her today.

52
00:02:29,246 --> 00:02:31,327
Hey, take her upstairs.

53
00:02:31,327 --> 00:02:32,332
Eun Ae, let's go upstairs.

54
00:02:33,127 --> 00:02:35,393
Where do you think you're going?
I'm not finished yet.

55
00:02:35,670 --> 00:02:37,950
Mom, what's wrong? What happened?

56
00:02:38,849 --> 00:02:40,861
I can't deal with this.

57
00:02:41,027 --> 00:02:44,097
Eun Nim, go get a cup of cold water.

58
00:02:44,427 --> 00:02:45,427
Yes, Grandma.

59
00:02:49,093 --> 00:02:50,520
Stop crying.

60
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:52,567
Your mother is upset because she cares.

61
00:02:54,259 --> 00:02:56,359
I know...

62
00:02:57,167 --> 00:02:59,534
But it's not like I wanted things
to turn out this way.

63
00:03:00,793 --> 00:03:04,060
I wanted to do well and be recognized too.

64
00:03:07,693 --> 00:03:10,493
How did you get released
so quickly anyway?

65
00:03:11,093 --> 00:03:12,626
Did Kangsu Construction settle?

66
00:03:13,027 --> 00:03:14,560
- Yes.
- All of a sudden?

67
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:16,206
Without any conditions?

68
00:03:16,359 --> 00:03:17,459
There were conditions, of course.

69
00:03:18,420 --> 00:03:20,886
I accepted them.

70
00:03:21,369 --> 00:03:22,536
What were they?

71
00:03:22,860 --> 00:03:26,127
I don't know what happened,
but don't be too harsh.

72
00:03:26,498 --> 00:03:28,527
Even between parents and children,

73
00:03:28,527 --> 00:03:31,735
words shot like arrows stay in the heart.

74
00:03:31,735 --> 00:03:33,754
What choice did I have?

75
00:03:33,754 --> 00:03:35,360
That foolish girl got scammed...

76
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:37,851
by her business partner, lost her company,

77
00:03:38,227 --> 00:03:41,323
and even ended up in detention.

78
00:03:41,323 --> 00:03:43,627
Detention? You mean jail?

79
00:03:43,627 --> 00:03:46,460
Mom, what are you talking about?
Eun Ae got scammed?

80
00:03:46,460 --> 00:03:47,863
What do you mean detention?

81
00:03:47,863 --> 00:03:49,029
Drink.

82
00:03:50,779 --> 00:03:51,779
Hey, Dad.

83
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:54,301
There's a limit to how much disappointment
I can take.

84
00:03:54,301 --> 00:03:55,960
I didn't ask for anything special.

85
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:58,038
I never asked her
to live up to her siblings.

86
00:03:58,038 --> 00:03:59,727
Just something ordinary...

87
00:03:59,727 --> 00:04:02,068
That's how children are.

88
00:04:02,068 --> 00:04:05,027
Even from the same womb,
they all turn out different.

89
00:04:11,151 --> 00:04:13,386
(Kangsu Construction)

90
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:15,055
Are your mom and sister okay?

91
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:17,135
No, they're not.

92
00:04:17,639 --> 00:04:19,872
Mom hit Eun Ae, and she was crying.

93
00:04:21,027 --> 00:04:22,693
Is it true that her company was taken?

94
00:04:23,593 --> 00:04:25,360
Why was she in detention?

95
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:28,327
You can hear about that
once Eun Ae calms down.

96
00:04:29,326 --> 00:04:31,905
Can you make her breakfast
before you go to school?

97
00:04:32,693 --> 00:04:35,675
Your sister
probably hasn't eaten properly.

98
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:37,893
Okay, I will.

99
00:04:40,093 --> 00:04:42,315
What on earth happened, Cho Eun Ae?

100
00:04:55,393 --> 00:04:56,763
Thank you, Team Manager.

101
00:04:56,763 --> 00:05:00,072
Thanks to you,
my daughter was released this morning.

102
00:05:00,072 --> 00:05:01,106
That's a relief.

103
00:05:01,370 --> 00:05:03,737
Actually,
could I get your daughter's number?

104
00:05:04,027 --> 00:05:06,727
Eun Ae's number?

105
00:05:06,727 --> 00:05:07,741
Why do you ask?

106
00:05:08,613 --> 00:05:09,613
Well,

107
00:05:10,727 --> 00:05:12,579
there's something I need to check
before she comes to work.

108
00:05:13,093 --> 00:05:14,093
Sure.

109
00:05:14,293 --> 00:05:16,260
Her number is...

110
00:05:17,580 --> 00:05:18,652
Zero, one, zero...

111
00:05:19,660 --> 00:05:21,193
Nine, four, seven, eight...

112
00:05:22,427 --> 00:05:23,427
Thank you.

113
00:05:24,193 --> 00:05:27,127
Don't worry too much.
I'll take care of everything.

114
00:05:27,587 --> 00:05:28,587
Yes.

115
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:33,300
Chief Ko,

116
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:35,927
thank you for your leniency.

117
00:05:37,139 --> 00:05:38,506
- Let's begin the meeting.
- Okay.

118
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:42,160
I'll get going then.

119
00:05:48,448 --> 00:05:49,449
(Strategic Planning Division,
Organizational Chart)

120
00:05:49,449 --> 00:05:52,293
This is the final team structure
that Team Manager Ko and I...

121
00:05:52,679 --> 00:05:53,812
just agreed on.

122
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:57,457
May I ask why
the members' opinions weren't considered?

123
00:05:57,693 --> 00:06:00,693
Of course,
if I were only in a supervisory role,

124
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:02,527
I might have considered it.

125
00:06:02,527 --> 00:06:05,727
But as someone who also serves
as a team manager,

126
00:06:05,993 --> 00:06:08,627
I need you,
who I've worked closely with, Ms. Seo.

127
00:06:08,986 --> 00:06:09,986
Does that answer your question?

128
00:06:12,606 --> 00:06:14,793
Team Two is short one person.

129
00:06:14,793 --> 00:06:18,313
Team Manager Ko will assign personnel
if needed.

130
00:06:18,601 --> 00:06:19,746
Any other questions?

131
00:06:19,746 --> 00:06:20,746
Just one more.

132
00:06:20,993 --> 00:06:23,060
For Team Two, both Team Manager Ko
and developer Cho Eun Ae...

133
00:06:23,460 --> 00:06:24,993
are new to Kangsu Construction.

134
00:06:25,660 --> 00:06:26,793
To be fair...

135
00:06:26,793 --> 00:06:29,222
Since this TF is starting with two teams,

136
00:06:29,886 --> 00:06:31,358
I plan to approach it
in a completely new way,

137
00:06:31,358 --> 00:06:33,160
different from Kangsu Construction's
usual methods.

138
00:06:33,846 --> 00:06:36,780
That's why I wanted members
who aren't used to Kangsu Construction,

139
00:06:37,666 --> 00:06:38,732
and I'm very satisfied.

140
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:42,133
I noted Team Manager Ko's opinion,

141
00:06:42,527 --> 00:06:45,099
but also considered what Ms. Seo said.

142
00:06:45,565 --> 00:06:47,432
So Ha Yu Ju, in her first year,
is joining Team One,

143
00:06:47,793 --> 00:06:49,442
Assistant Manager Kim, in his third year,
is joining Team Two,

144
00:06:49,727 --> 00:06:53,079
and one developer is assigned
to each team.

145
00:06:54,193 --> 00:06:55,260
Perfect.

146
00:06:55,260 --> 00:06:58,293
Then once the Joy developers join,

147
00:06:58,293 --> 00:07:00,720
we'll officially launch the TF.

148
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:02,500
Yes.

149
00:07:03,852 --> 00:07:05,119
What? Fake employment?

150
00:07:05,540 --> 00:07:07,376
Yeah, looking at the contract,

151
00:07:07,376 --> 00:07:10,030
except for Joy,
nothing belongs to Kangsu Construction.

152
00:07:10,727 --> 00:07:13,527
While developing Joy,

153
00:07:13,527 --> 00:07:15,193
I encrypted and stored
a lot of follow-up ideas.

154
00:07:15,193 --> 00:07:17,613
So you're saying
you'll join as an intern first...

155
00:07:17,613 --> 00:07:19,539
and retrieve those?

156
00:07:19,539 --> 00:07:23,060
Yes. Right now,
I can't even access the server.

157
00:07:23,060 --> 00:07:24,113
It's the only way.

158
00:07:24,580 --> 00:07:26,580
- And then?
- I'll start over.

159
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:29,893
I'll retrieve everything within a month
and get back on my feet.

160
00:07:29,893 --> 00:07:32,293
The plan sounds good,
but what about capital?

161
00:07:32,693 --> 00:07:34,293
Even if you're starting from scratch,

162
00:07:34,293 --> 00:07:36,527
you still need basic funds
to get a company going.

163
00:07:36,527 --> 00:07:39,227
I've thought it all through,
so just watch.

164
00:07:39,612 --> 00:07:41,145
Watch how I rise again.

165
00:07:49,953 --> 00:07:52,764
Fruits of Giving Foundation?

166
00:08:01,181 --> 00:08:02,749
(Certificate of Appreciation,
To Cho Eun Hyeong)

167
00:08:02,749 --> 00:08:04,584
(For your dedication to helping,
those in need over the past ten years.)

168
00:08:10,212 --> 00:08:11,212
Mom.

169
00:08:12,406 --> 00:08:14,204
Hey, you're home early.

170
00:08:14,427 --> 00:08:16,560
I drew you at kindergarten today.

171
00:08:18,306 --> 00:08:19,493
Ta-da.

172
00:08:19,493 --> 00:08:21,034
Am I really this pretty?

173
00:08:21,034 --> 00:08:24,427
Yes, among all my friends' moms,
you're the prettiest.

174
00:08:25,327 --> 00:08:28,460
You have to see fruit with your own eyes
to pick the best ones.

175
00:08:29,990 --> 00:08:30,990
What's this?

176
00:08:32,866 --> 00:08:34,033
I wonder what it is.

177
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:37,693
The paper looks really fancy,
even gold-embossed.

178
00:08:39,593 --> 00:08:41,927
Bit Na, should we go inside and change?

179
00:08:42,293 --> 00:08:44,693
You can change by yourself, right?

180
00:08:45,127 --> 00:08:46,127
Yes, Mom.

181
00:08:49,860 --> 00:08:52,393
Any other places you've donated to
besides this?

182
00:08:53,493 --> 00:08:55,019
Just a few.

183
00:08:55,827 --> 00:08:58,493
They're all small amounts,
just a little from the heart.

184
00:08:59,660 --> 00:09:02,427
Maybe 300 dollars a month
for allowance was too much.

185
00:09:02,593 --> 00:09:04,793
You've been donating here and there
every month.

186
00:09:05,566 --> 00:09:08,833
Honey,
I just wanted to help those in need.

187
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:10,432
What? Those in need?

188
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:14,627
Cho Eun Hyeong, I'm the one in need.
Do you know that?

189
00:09:14,627 --> 00:09:16,460
What are you talking about?
Why would you be?

190
00:09:16,460 --> 00:09:18,427
As a daughter-in-law, mother, and wife
who only knows work,

191
00:09:18,427 --> 00:09:20,260
I must be the most materialistic person
in your eyes.

192
00:09:22,993 --> 00:09:26,560
Do your parents know
your lectures are being canceled?

193
00:09:27,227 --> 00:09:30,827
I told Dad, but not Mom yet.

194
00:10:05,540 --> 00:10:06,940
Actually,

195
00:10:08,060 --> 00:10:10,060
I stopped by there not long ago,

196
00:10:10,827 --> 00:10:12,393
where that restaurant used to be.

197
00:10:17,432 --> 00:10:20,953
I was just passing by
and decided to drop in.

198
00:10:27,353 --> 00:10:28,387
You called for me, sir?

199
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:30,897
Hi, you're here.

200
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:34,633
This house...

201
00:10:35,827 --> 00:10:38,393
was designed by Manager Han,
Gyeol's father.

202
00:10:40,359 --> 00:10:42,326
It's gotten as old as I have now.

203
00:10:46,159 --> 00:10:48,559
I have something important...

204
00:10:49,393 --> 00:10:51,060
I need to ask of you.

205
00:10:54,565 --> 00:10:56,365
What's wrong with this?

206
00:11:01,662 --> 00:11:03,396
Are you taking that to Father?

207
00:11:04,086 --> 00:11:05,793
He's been outside too long.

208
00:11:05,793 --> 00:11:07,893
If he catches a cold, it'll be a problem.

209
00:11:07,893 --> 00:11:11,304
Mr. Seo came by earlier,
and it sounded like a serious discussion.

210
00:11:11,686 --> 00:11:14,941
Really?
I should at least bring some warm tea.

211
00:11:16,493 --> 00:11:17,693
Mother, should I do it?

212
00:11:20,414 --> 00:11:21,548
What's gotten into you lately?

213
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:23,550
Sorry? What do you mean?

214
00:11:23,927 --> 00:11:25,293
Just do as you usually do.

215
00:11:29,753 --> 00:11:33,053
Like I want to be like this.

216
00:11:34,825 --> 00:11:38,258
You're telling me to start over?
Hadn't you given up?

217
00:11:38,827 --> 00:11:40,427
I had.

218
00:11:40,427 --> 00:11:43,770
I searched for decades and found nothing.

219
00:11:45,227 --> 00:11:46,727
This is the last time.

220
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:50,944
Before I die,
I absolutely have to find her.

221
00:11:51,327 --> 00:11:54,013
You've already done everything you could.

222
00:11:55,499 --> 00:11:58,832
I know,
but I'll treat it like the first time...

223
00:11:59,427 --> 00:12:03,523
and start over from scratch, thoroughly.

224
00:12:04,234 --> 00:12:07,167
But absolutely no one can know.

225
00:12:08,760 --> 00:12:11,227
I don't want to raise expectations
and disappoint again.

226
00:12:12,219 --> 00:12:16,019
Yes, I understand.

227
00:12:21,446 --> 00:12:23,343
It's still chilly outside.

228
00:12:24,393 --> 00:12:26,860
Have some warm tea while you talk.

229
00:12:27,884 --> 00:12:31,017
Why did you come out?
We're going in soon anyway.

230
00:12:31,560 --> 00:12:34,327
Thanks to you, I'll get some sunlight.

231
00:12:35,493 --> 00:12:39,093
Were you talking about something secret?
Did I interrupt?

232
00:12:39,993 --> 00:12:41,742
Why would you be an intruder, Yeong Hwa?

233
00:12:41,927 --> 00:12:45,231
Why do you keep calling me by name?
It's embarrassing.

234
00:12:46,260 --> 00:12:47,460
It's a lovely sight, madam.

235
00:12:47,893 --> 00:12:50,260
See? Even Mr. Seo says so.

236
00:12:51,560 --> 00:12:54,060
From now on, you call me by my name too.

237
00:12:54,993 --> 00:12:55,993
Say, "Kang Su."

238
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:59,060
What? You're being ridiculous.

239
00:12:59,060 --> 00:13:02,127
Go on, try it. "Kang Su."

240
00:13:04,753 --> 00:13:06,353
What is wrong with you?

241
00:13:14,760 --> 00:13:16,626
Dae Chi, you're home.

242
00:13:16,860 --> 00:13:20,029
Yes, I'm home, Father, Mother.

243
00:13:22,827 --> 00:13:24,427
What were you talking about so happily?

244
00:13:25,271 --> 00:13:28,274
You're home early. Let's go inside.

245
00:13:29,499 --> 00:13:30,765
Mr. Seo, you can leave for the day.

246
00:13:31,012 --> 00:13:33,279
Rest well, Chairman, madam.

247
00:13:33,660 --> 00:13:35,260
Take care on your way, Mr. Seo.

248
00:13:46,493 --> 00:13:47,493
Seo Gwon Sik.

249
00:13:50,927 --> 00:13:52,160
What were you talking about?

250
00:13:53,427 --> 00:13:55,535
What was so funny
that you were laughing like that...

251
00:13:55,535 --> 00:13:58,193
until I came in?

252
00:13:58,460 --> 00:14:00,060
It was just a trivial joke.

253
00:14:00,060 --> 00:14:01,127
A trivial joke.

254
00:14:02,060 --> 00:14:05,527
Can't I hear that trivial joke too?

255
00:14:05,813 --> 00:14:06,946
What's gotten into you, sir?

256
00:14:07,260 --> 00:14:08,260
What's gotten into me?

257
00:14:09,693 --> 00:14:12,193
The way you've been acting is ridiculous,
that's why.

258
00:14:15,593 --> 00:14:16,727
Listen.

259
00:14:16,727 --> 00:14:19,960
No matter how close you and Father are
as his right-hand man,

260
00:14:20,893 --> 00:14:23,193
in the end, I'll be
the one presiding over his funeral.

261
00:14:24,832 --> 00:14:26,799
I'm the one
who'll perform the ancestral rites.

262
00:14:27,193 --> 00:14:29,093
What are you saying right now?

263
00:14:29,093 --> 00:14:31,560
I, Ko Dae Chi,
am my father's only bloodline,

264
00:14:33,627 --> 00:14:36,393
which means
Kangsu Group is ultimately mine.

265
00:14:37,660 --> 00:14:38,760
I'll take my leave.

266
00:14:39,812 --> 00:14:41,080
Are you going to keep ignoring me
to the end?

267
00:14:41,593 --> 00:14:42,627
Hey, Seo Gwon Sik!

268
00:14:50,519 --> 00:14:51,519
It hurts.

269
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:55,593
Earlier, I saw Mr. Seo and Father...

270
00:14:55,593 --> 00:14:58,060
talking in the garden for quite a while.

271
00:14:58,393 --> 00:14:59,899
Do you know what that was about?

272
00:15:00,460 --> 00:15:02,546
How would I know?

273
00:15:03,227 --> 00:15:06,254
Sometimes it feels like Father...

274
00:15:06,254 --> 00:15:07,893
treats Mr. Seo more like a son than you.

275
00:15:08,827 --> 00:15:10,000
Stop talking nonsense...

276
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:12,493
and focus on treating Mother well.

277
00:15:12,493 --> 00:15:15,502
That remaining 20 percent depends on her.

278
00:15:15,502 --> 00:15:16,827
Whatever.

279
00:15:16,827 --> 00:15:19,060
I'm going out of my way
to flatter someone I normally wouldn't.

280
00:15:19,486 --> 00:15:21,754
That's why I hate the idea of a concubine.

281
00:15:21,754 --> 00:15:23,003
Watch what you say.

282
00:15:23,493 --> 00:15:26,226
She was legally married
and remarried properly.

283
00:15:26,226 --> 00:15:29,027
But she's not your biological mother.

284
00:15:29,293 --> 00:15:31,330
As you know,

285
00:15:31,560 --> 00:15:33,927
my father fell
for my mom's young caregiver,

286
00:15:34,127 --> 00:15:36,760
even had a son in secret.
What happened after that?

287
00:15:37,127 --> 00:15:39,860
Crystal, it's time you let that go.

288
00:15:39,860 --> 00:15:41,407
How can I?

289
00:15:41,727 --> 00:15:43,693
That nightmare is about to repeat itself.

290
00:15:45,093 --> 00:15:46,760
Eun Su Jeong, Crystal.

291
00:15:47,257 --> 00:15:49,605
You have me by your side now.

292
00:15:49,605 --> 00:15:50,950
Back then, you had no one,

293
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:54,060
but now you have me,
Ko Dae Chi, your husband.

294
00:15:54,060 --> 00:15:56,893
Really? So I can just trust you?

295
00:15:56,893 --> 00:15:57,893
Of course!

296
00:15:58,927 --> 00:16:01,260
No one can touch what I've built.

297
00:16:01,530 --> 00:16:04,130
Ko Dae Chi, Eun Su Jeong, Ko Min Ho.
Our own fortress!

298
00:16:04,293 --> 00:16:07,260
Really? That's amazing, honey.

299
00:16:07,260 --> 00:16:08,260
If you think so, come here.

300
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:10,536
Just stay in my arms.

301
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:13,105
- My husband is the best.
- Don't worry.

302
00:16:13,105 --> 00:16:14,239
Stay quiet and don't talk.

303
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:17,667
I'm sorry I couldn't tell you.

304
00:16:18,527 --> 00:16:21,527
I asked Dad to keep it a secret, Mom.

305
00:16:21,993 --> 00:16:24,584
I really didn't want to disappoint you.

306
00:16:24,584 --> 00:16:27,593
So you stabbed me in the back instead?

307
00:16:27,593 --> 00:16:28,627
More importantly,

308
00:16:28,927 --> 00:16:31,160
what is this about? You're going to work
at Kangsu Construction?

309
00:16:31,293 --> 00:16:32,327
Well,

310
00:16:32,860 --> 00:16:36,327
it seems Kangsu Construction
evaluated my program positively,

311
00:16:36,727 --> 00:16:39,760
so they want me, the developer,
to join as well.

312
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:41,500
That's a silver lining at least.

313
00:16:41,760 --> 00:16:44,837
What if you'd lost your company
and ended up unemployed?

314
00:16:44,837 --> 00:16:47,660
- Exactly.
- That just shows how capable Eun Ae is.

315
00:16:47,660 --> 00:16:50,793
How impressive must it have been
for them to make the offer first...

316
00:16:50,793 --> 00:16:53,646
For now, keep your mouth shut.

317
00:16:54,126 --> 00:16:55,126
What?

318
00:16:55,126 --> 00:16:57,227
I can be disappointed in my children,

319
00:16:57,227 --> 00:16:59,660
but I won't tolerate you disappointing me.

320
00:17:03,627 --> 00:17:07,127
Hello? Who is this?

321
00:17:09,860 --> 00:17:12,827
This is unexpected.
How did you get my number?

322
00:17:12,827 --> 00:17:14,493
I asked your father earlier today.

323
00:17:16,460 --> 00:17:17,793
Let me thank you first.

324
00:17:18,372 --> 00:17:19,405
Thank you.

325
00:17:20,820 --> 00:17:23,609
Thanks for settling the case
and even offering me a job.

326
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:25,960
I only facilitated the settlement.
I didn't agree to it,

327
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:26,993
strictly speaking.

328
00:17:28,120 --> 00:17:30,720
He has a way of speaking
that makes things unpleasant.

329
00:17:31,987 --> 00:17:34,387
Did you have something to say to me?

330
00:17:34,660 --> 00:17:37,460
I'm curious why
you suddenly accepted my offer.

331
00:17:37,820 --> 00:17:39,120
- What?
- You know,

332
00:17:39,427 --> 00:17:41,928
when I first offered you
the intern position, you were furious.

333
00:17:42,097 --> 00:17:43,829
So it's strange you changed your mind
in just a few hours.

334
00:17:45,527 --> 00:17:46,974
Because I didn't want a criminal record...

335
00:17:46,974 --> 00:17:50,260
You seemed far too bold for that
to be the only reason.

336
00:17:50,919 --> 00:17:52,619
I have nothing left to lose.

337
00:17:54,186 --> 00:17:55,686
Haven't you heard?

338
00:17:56,113 --> 00:17:58,077
The scariest person is someone
with nothing to lose.

339
00:18:00,060 --> 00:18:02,782
From now on,
I will live one day at a time.

340
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:05,827
Stop joking and tell me the real reason.

341
00:18:05,827 --> 00:18:07,160
Why did you change your mind?

342
00:18:07,327 --> 00:18:10,827
Even if I fought Kangsu Construction
in court,

343
00:18:11,299 --> 00:18:13,127
it'd be like throwing an egg at a rock.

344
00:18:13,660 --> 00:18:16,495
What else could I do if I didn't accept?

345
00:18:18,327 --> 00:18:21,260
Fine. I'll believe that's the truth.

346
00:18:22,427 --> 00:18:24,303
You made the offer. That should be enough.

347
00:18:24,303 --> 00:18:25,605
No need to nitpick.

348
00:18:26,093 --> 00:18:27,960
If you cause any trouble,

349
00:18:28,174 --> 00:18:30,960
it'll put me in a very difficult position.

350
00:18:31,127 --> 00:18:32,127
Excuse me.

351
00:18:32,812 --> 00:18:34,614
You said a lion shouldn't feel sorry...

352
00:18:34,614 --> 00:18:36,315
for eating a rabbit, right?

353
00:18:36,315 --> 00:18:37,383
Yes.

354
00:18:38,807 --> 00:18:40,186
Then I'm the rabbit.

355
00:18:41,593 --> 00:18:43,727
So why would you be afraid...

356
00:18:43,727 --> 00:18:45,327
of such a cute rabbit?

357
00:18:46,172 --> 00:18:50,974
I'm a very weak and fragile rabbit.

358
00:18:51,964 --> 00:18:54,900
Who said I was afraid?
I was just confirming...

359
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:56,427
If you're done, let's go.

360
00:18:59,327 --> 00:19:00,927
I'll pay for the tea...

361
00:19:01,547 --> 00:19:04,713
as thanks for letting me see
the light of day again.

362
00:19:07,393 --> 00:19:08,714
Cutting me off mid-sentence...

363
00:19:09,993 --> 00:19:11,260
What's cute about that?

364
00:19:17,227 --> 00:19:18,260
Fragile?

365
00:19:20,120 --> 00:19:21,594
This is unbelievable.

366
00:19:26,386 --> 00:19:27,986
Careful, it's hot.

367
00:19:33,593 --> 00:19:34,974
It's not good this time either?

368
00:19:34,974 --> 00:19:36,760
It's fine. It's healthy.

369
00:19:40,293 --> 00:19:41,727
If you're not sleeping, let's talk.

370
00:19:42,759 --> 00:19:43,820
I know.

371
00:19:44,893 --> 00:19:48,727
You're more thoughtful and caring
toward the kids than I am.

372
00:19:49,566 --> 00:19:50,790
Still,

373
00:19:51,127 --> 00:19:53,160
how could you two fool me like that?

374
00:19:53,727 --> 00:19:54,922
Honey.

375
00:19:54,922 --> 00:19:56,140
Don't say anything and go to sleep.

376
00:19:57,293 --> 00:20:00,760
Eun Ae got scouted by Kangsu Construction,

377
00:20:01,207 --> 00:20:02,722
so let's pretend this never happened.

378
00:20:03,159 --> 00:20:05,026
I'm letting this go...

379
00:20:05,227 --> 00:20:07,193
with a big heart.

380
00:20:09,027 --> 00:20:10,576
Thank you for understanding.

381
00:20:13,333 --> 00:20:14,333
But then,

382
00:20:14,927 --> 00:20:17,950
what's that perfume smell
coming from your shirt?

383
00:20:19,627 --> 00:20:21,420
Perfume?

384
00:20:21,420 --> 00:20:24,156
Yes, perfume.
Your shirt smells like it these days.

385
00:20:24,427 --> 00:20:27,727
You said
I smelled like disinfectant lately,

386
00:20:28,493 --> 00:20:29,493
so I sprayed that.

387
00:20:29,493 --> 00:20:31,227
The air freshener.

388
00:20:32,980 --> 00:20:33,980
Air freshener?

389
00:20:35,319 --> 00:20:37,169
I can't believe this.

390
00:20:38,127 --> 00:20:39,427
That smell was from that?

391
00:20:41,839 --> 00:20:43,742
What am I supposed to do wearing this?

392
00:20:46,699 --> 00:20:47,699
What's that?

393
00:20:48,114 --> 00:20:51,951
Su Jeong bought it for me
to take dance lessons together.

394
00:20:52,193 --> 00:20:53,779
Dance, all of a sudden?

395
00:20:53,779 --> 00:20:55,113
Exactly.

396
00:20:55,612 --> 00:20:59,158
She insists I do it with her.

397
00:20:59,539 --> 00:21:00,606
It's obvious why.

398
00:21:00,860 --> 00:21:03,393
She wants a servant
to follow her around like a queen.

399
00:21:04,259 --> 00:21:05,559
Then just don't do it.

400
00:21:05,919 --> 00:21:07,186
How can I?

401
00:21:08,127 --> 00:21:11,944
I'll just go along with it
and get what I can out of it.

402
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:19,478
Su Jeong was saying something strange...

403
00:21:19,478 --> 00:21:22,014
about where
the chairman's 20 percent stake might go.

404
00:21:22,960 --> 00:21:23,960
What?

405
00:21:23,960 --> 00:21:27,186
Did the chairman write a will
or something?

406
00:21:28,060 --> 00:21:29,855
Just stop and go to sleep.

407
00:21:30,393 --> 00:21:31,927
It's none of our concern.

408
00:21:32,893 --> 00:21:34,960
To be honest,
you're the chairman's right-hand man.

409
00:21:35,593 --> 00:21:38,127
He trusts you more than CEO Ko.

410
00:21:39,927 --> 00:21:42,060
Could that stake possibly go to you?

411
00:21:43,193 --> 00:21:44,227
Don't be ridiculous.

412
00:21:46,027 --> 00:21:48,407
I, Ko Dae Chi,
am my father's only bloodline,

413
00:21:48,793 --> 00:21:51,593
which means
Kangsu Group is ultimately mine.

414
00:21:53,360 --> 00:21:55,260
Don't expect anything.

415
00:21:56,293 --> 00:21:57,393
Just turn off the light.

416
00:21:57,660 --> 00:22:00,452
You can turn it off yourself.
You're right there.

417
00:22:01,032 --> 00:22:02,732
What, are your arms broken?

418
00:22:13,727 --> 00:22:16,168
Since this TF is starting with two teams,

419
00:22:16,751 --> 00:22:18,258
I plan to approach it
in a completely new way,

420
00:22:18,258 --> 00:22:20,093
different from Kangsu Construction's
usual methods.

421
00:22:20,793 --> 00:22:23,627
That's why I wanted members
who aren't used to Kangsu Construction,

422
00:22:24,627 --> 00:22:25,693
and I'm very satisfied.

423
00:22:34,787 --> 00:22:35,821
(Here's the webtoon project report,
Seung Ri.)

424
00:22:36,255 --> 00:22:38,455
(Webtoon Project Report by Seo Seung Wu,
"Secretary by Nature")

425
00:22:39,060 --> 00:22:40,626
(A comedy webtoon,
Based on workplace relationships)

426
00:22:44,860 --> 00:22:46,060
(Chairman, would you like some coffee?)

427
00:22:46,060 --> 00:22:47,860
(I made it with directly-sourced beans!)

428
00:22:50,627 --> 00:22:51,704
(Chairman! Nice shot!)

429
00:22:55,307 --> 00:22:56,309
(I brought your favorite taro soup.)

430
00:22:56,309 --> 00:22:57,514
(You should've put it in a thermos.)

431
00:22:57,514 --> 00:22:58,849
(I'm sorry, ma'am.
I'll be more careful next time.)

432
00:22:58,849 --> 00:23:00,379
(After taking Ppori for a walk,
please give him a bath too.)

433
00:23:00,379 --> 00:23:01,593
(Yes, I'll be back.)

434
00:23:05,660 --> 00:23:06,886
This idiot.

435
00:23:07,727 --> 00:23:10,723
By the way, when do you think...

436
00:23:10,993 --> 00:23:12,560
the identity of the author
of "The ER Witch" will be revealed?

437
00:23:13,860 --> 00:23:16,456
We won't know
until the author does a reveal.

438
00:23:18,860 --> 00:23:19,860
Want to make a bet?

439
00:23:20,327 --> 00:23:22,560
I bet 100 dollars...

440
00:23:22,760 --> 00:23:24,460
the author is actually a doctor.

441
00:23:25,360 --> 00:23:27,927
Hey, we're online here.

442
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:31,377
Then, how about meeting offline?

443
00:23:32,060 --> 00:23:34,060
As fellow "The ER Witch" fans,

444
00:23:34,560 --> 00:23:36,393
we could interact more actively.

445
00:23:37,133 --> 00:23:39,666
Meet up? What is he talking about?

446
00:23:40,593 --> 00:23:42,393
That'd be a bit difficult.

447
00:23:44,127 --> 00:23:46,960
I usually don't suggest
to meet offline either,

448
00:23:47,379 --> 00:23:50,350
but I'd really like to meet you
at least once.

449
00:23:50,873 --> 00:23:53,793
I have a feeling you're someone...

450
00:23:53,793 --> 00:23:55,267
with a pure soul, just like mine.

451
00:23:55,793 --> 00:23:57,693
I don't know about a pure soul,

452
00:23:57,693 --> 00:23:59,760
but I do get told
I have an innocent face...

453
00:24:02,027 --> 00:24:03,060
I must be crazy.

454
00:24:05,827 --> 00:24:07,993
It's late, so I'm logging off now.

455
00:24:11,827 --> 00:24:13,560
Going to bed early and waking up early.

456
00:24:14,227 --> 00:24:15,694
What a wholesome vibe.

457
00:24:20,227 --> 00:24:21,593
You were reading it?

458
00:24:22,493 --> 00:24:24,327
So, what do you think?
I'm a total genius, right?

459
00:24:26,627 --> 00:24:27,967
First, let's get to the point.

460
00:24:28,960 --> 00:24:30,703
I submitted the report,
so give me my allowance.

461
00:24:31,604 --> 00:24:32,827
Hey, Seo Seung Wu.

462
00:24:32,827 --> 00:24:34,340
What?

463
00:24:35,805 --> 00:24:38,093
Don't even try to back out...

464
00:24:38,093 --> 00:24:39,745
of your promise.

465
00:24:39,900 --> 00:24:41,580
Where are you planning to present this?

466
00:24:42,213 --> 00:24:43,682
I'm submitting it to a contest tomorrow.
Why?

467
00:24:43,927 --> 00:24:46,418
- Don't.
- What?

468
00:24:46,418 --> 00:24:49,627
What if you win and Mom and Dad see it?

469
00:24:49,627 --> 00:24:51,523
They'll be happy.

470
00:24:51,523 --> 00:24:53,692
"Our son finally escaped unemployment...

471
00:24:53,692 --> 00:24:56,993
and has become a true artist."

472
00:24:56,993 --> 00:24:58,760
What? Happy?

473
00:24:59,693 --> 00:25:01,227
Don't you have any other material?

474
00:25:01,693 --> 00:25:03,293
And when have Mom and Dad
ever been like this?

475
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:05,604
You made them look pathetic and desperate
in every scene.

476
00:25:05,604 --> 00:25:09,075
That's just exaggerated
for comedic effect.

477
00:25:09,860 --> 00:25:13,178
I'm warning you. Don't submit it, got it?

478
00:25:13,460 --> 00:25:14,493
What are you saying?

479
00:25:15,660 --> 00:25:17,297
You're so petty!

480
00:25:17,627 --> 00:25:20,527
You're just trying to avoid giving me
my allowance, aren't you?

481
00:25:20,527 --> 00:25:22,393
Where do you think you're going
with that attitude?

482
00:25:22,393 --> 00:25:23,721
- You!
- Let go.

483
00:25:23,721 --> 00:25:25,591
I said don't do it.

484
00:25:25,591 --> 00:25:27,893
- Darn it!
- Did you kick me?

485
00:25:27,893 --> 00:25:29,260
Why I ought to...

486
00:25:29,660 --> 00:25:31,110
Just give me my allowance!

487
00:25:32,460 --> 00:25:34,566
You complete idiot.

488
00:25:35,100 --> 00:25:37,403
(Kangsu Construction)

489
00:25:37,403 --> 00:25:40,027
Having a Kangsu Construction employee ID
or not...

490
00:25:40,027 --> 00:25:41,140
makes all the difference.

491
00:25:43,319 --> 00:25:44,319
Hello.

492
00:25:45,267 --> 00:25:46,667
Why are you here again?

493
00:25:49,060 --> 00:25:50,060
I look forward to working with you.

494
00:25:56,393 --> 00:25:57,393
Bye then.

495
00:26:02,426 --> 00:26:03,863
Good morning, Team Manager.

496
00:26:06,427 --> 00:26:08,801
Don't do that. It's not cute at all.

497
00:26:09,460 --> 00:26:10,634
Why not?

498
00:26:11,060 --> 00:26:13,460
Look closer. I might seem cuter.

499
00:26:14,773 --> 00:26:15,773
Seriously.

500
00:26:16,627 --> 00:26:17,627
Good morning.

501
00:26:20,393 --> 00:26:21,721
Hello, Chief Ko.

502
00:26:54,513 --> 00:26:57,516
(Our Happy Days)

503
00:26:57,516 --> 00:26:58,627
I'm Cho Eun Ae.

504
00:26:58,627 --> 00:27:00,986
I'm determined to dedicate myself
to Kangsu Construction.

505
00:27:00,986 --> 00:27:03,160
What dedication for a six-month intern?

506
00:27:03,527 --> 00:27:04,827
Just one month.

507
00:27:05,160 --> 00:27:07,259
Finally, I get to see my baby Joy again.

508
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:10,827
Your heart must be torn by now.

509
00:27:10,927 --> 00:27:11,927
Hey!

510
00:27:11,927 --> 00:27:13,599
You perverted psycho!

511
00:27:13,765 --> 00:27:15,467
- Try to make up nicely.
- I can't.

512
00:27:16,060 --> 00:27:18,937
But why are you being so nice to me?

513
00:27:18,937 --> 00:27:21,464
As a senior at Kangsu Construction,
it's only natural to help a junior.

514
00:27:21,573 --> 00:27:22,608
Think of me as your mentor.

515
00:27:23,393 --> 00:27:27,346
I have something to say to everyone.

516
00:27:27,846 --> 00:27:29,314
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
